HEADWORD: Chamberer
<hw>Cham"ber*er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One
who attends in a chamber; a chambermaid.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A civilian; a carpetmonger.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chambering</ent>⟦br⟧
